ng disruptions to businesses of all sizes around the world, the new platform will help African business owners prosper, by enabling access to effective and convenient digital payment and transaction solutions and technologies. Quickteller Business will also offer a three-month zero transaction fee incentive for SMEs that sign up now, as part of its launch offer.” By Peter Egwuatu Interswitch Group, Africa’s leading technology-driven company focused on the digitization of payments in Africa, has announced the launch of Quickteller Business, a new comprehensive corporate solution focused on empowering businesses of all sizes, facilitate payments and manage transactions from anywhere in the world – through one, simple… February 16, 2021 In "News" NIGERIA has had long standing gaps in the availability of credit or loans to individuals and businesses within underserved demographics of the Nigerian population; this has led people to experience difficulties in accessing unsecured, short-term micro-loans from financial institutions. October 18, 2017 In "Technology" Interswitch, Africa’s leading integrated payment processing and transaction switching company has been appraised at Maturity Level 3 on the CMMI Institute’s Capability Maturity Model Integration (CMMI) framework August 18, 2015 In "News"